        can contain arbitrary text and any of the following conversion
        specifications:
        %%AA           The full weekday name.

        %%aa           The abbreviated weekday name, where the abbreviation is
                     the first three characters.

        %%BB           The full month name.

        %%bb or %%hh     The abbreviated month name, where the abbreviation is the
                     first three characters.

        %%CC           The first two digits of the year, indicating the century.

        %%cc           Equivalent to %%mm//%%dd//%%yy.

        %%DD           The date in the format mm/dd/yy.

        %%dd           The day of the month as a decimal number (01-31).

        %%ee           The day of month as a decimal number (1-31); single
                     digits are preceded by a blank.

        %%HH           The hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (00-23).

        %%II           The hour (12-hour clock) as a decimal number (01-12).

        %%jj           The day of the year as a decimal number (001-366).

        %%kk           The hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (0-23);
