    The format string for the default display is:

    %a %b %e %H:%M:%S %Z %Y%n

  NNOOTTEESS

    Only users who have been granted the permission SE_SYSTEMTIME_PRIVILEGE
    can set the date and time.

    The specifiers %c, %D, %x, and %y all represent the year as a two-digit
    variable. Examine any shell scripts that make use of this output to ensure
    that they will function correctly.

    In the POSIX or C locale, the appropriate date representation is %%mm//%%dd//%%yy;
    the appropriate time representation is %%HH::%%MM::%%SS.

